
                                            More than 120,000 people are expected to attend the event where ZCC head bishop Barnabas Lekganyane is expected to be a keynote speaker.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - The Johannesburg Metro Police Department (JMPD) has warned motorists that roads around the FNB Stadium will be closed on Sunday, as members of the ZCC attend a national prayer session. More than 120,000 people are expected to attend the event where ZCC head bishop Barnabas Lekganyane is expected to be a keynote speaker. The JMPD says some roads, including the Soweto highway and Booysens Road, will be affected.Spokesperson Wayne Minaar says roads will be reopened after 4pm on Sunday. “Officers will be on duty to manage traffic during the national day of prayer at 4pm at FNB Stadium. Motorists are urged to drive with caution at control points.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)